Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
saveWhatIfConstraints(25.10)                      saveWhatIfConstraints(25.10)

Name
       saveWhatIfConstraints  - Saves the what-if timing constraints in Design
       Compiler format

Syntax
        saveWhatIfConstraints

       [<blackBoxCellName>]

       [-pt | -dc]

       [-dir <dirName>]

       [-filePrefix <prefix>]

       Saves the what-if timing constraints in Design Compiler format. You can
       use this command after the module definition of  the  blackbox  or  the
       blackblob is available with the I/O's in the Verilog netlist.

Parameters
       <blackBoxCellName>
              Specifies the name of the blackbox or blackblob cell.

              Default: If you do not specify a name for the blackbox or black-
              blob  cell,  constraints are saved for all blackbox or blackblob
              cells.

       -dir <dirName>
              Specifies the name of the directory  in  which  the  constraints
              file  will  be  generated. This directory must reside within the
              current working directory.

              Default: The constraints file is saved in  the  current  working
              directory.

       -filePrefix <prefix>
              Specifies  the prefix for the constraints file name. This prefix
              is added to the name of the blackbox or blackblob cell to gener-
              ate the name of the constraints file. For example, if you  spec-
              ify  the  prefix  constraintsFile  and the blackbox or blackblob
              cell name is Block1, the name of the  file  in  which  the  con-
              straints  are  saved  will  be  constraintsFileBlock1.pt or con-
              straintsFileBlock1.dc.

              Default: If you do not specify a prefix, the constraints file is
              saved as <blackBoxCellName>.pt or  <blackBoxCellName>.dc,  where
              <blackBoxCellName>  is  the  name  of  the blackbox or blackblob
              cell.

       -pt | -dc
              Specifies the constraint format.

              Default: Constraints are saved both in PT and DC format.

Related Information
              * What-If Timing Analysis chapter in the Innovus User Guide

